  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Intra-epidermal nerve fiber density can be assessed using skin biopsy. A decrease of this
      density is used to diagnose small fiber neuropathy, despite the absence of normative data in
      a selected normal population. To establish a normative set of data matched for age and sex is
      absolutely needed to evaluate the sensibility and specificity of this test.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
